Task 3: Role of CPU, RAM, and GPU in Gaming

•	CPU
The CPU is known as the brain of the computer. When playing games like PUBG or Free Fire, it processes player actions, game logic, and other background tasks. A faster CPU helps the game run smoothly.

•	RAM
RAM stores the temporary data required by the game while it is running. Having enough RAM helps reduce lag and allows the game to load resources quickly. Most modern games perform well with at least 16GB of RAM.

•	GPU
The GPU is responsible for displaying graphics, textures, and visual effects. In games such as PUBG, a powerful GPU provides higher FPS and better graphics quality, making the gaming experience smoother.












