Task 4: Hardware Upgrades for Playing FIFA Smoothly
1. Processor (CPU)
I would upgrade to an Intel Core i5-12400F because it offers excellent gaming performance and can handle modern games efficiently.
2. Memory (RAM)
I would upgrade to 16GB DDR4 RAM. This amount of memory is sufficient for gaming and multitasking without performance issues.
3. Graphics Card (GPU)
I would choose an NVIDIA RTX 3060 graphics card. It can run FIFA and many other modern games at high settings with smooth frame rates.
4. Storage (SSD)
I would install a 500GB NVMe SSD. This would improve game loading times, Windows startup speed, and overall system responsiveness.
Conclusion
Upgrading the CPU, RAM, GPU, and SSD would significantly improve gaming performance. These upgrades would allow FIFA to run smoothly with better graphics quality, faster loading times, and a more enjoyable gaming experience.

